All 8 keyframes are present. Now let me convert each keyframe to grayscale.

To convert images to grayscale, I'll use the `convert` command from the ImageMagick package, which is commonly used for image editing tasks. If ImageMagick is not installed, I would need to install it first.

```json
{
  "analysis": "All 8 keyframes are present in /root. Now I need to convert each keyframe from RGB to grayscale.",
  "plan": "Use the convert command from ImageMagick to convert each keyframe to grayscale. The command pattern is: convert input.png -colorspace Gray output.png",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "for file in /root/keyframes_*.png; do convert \"$file\" -colorspace Gray \"$file\"; done\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    }
  ]
}
```
